reviews.text:
On the One hundred and second floor (102) of ICC, the Tosca experience will amaze you on every metric.  
There's the suspense building wait in the elevator ride to level 103, the walk through the lobby at the Ritz, the escalator down to the hostess followed by the short walk through a labyrinth of rich decor that opens into a double story open space with the most incredible views of Hong Kong island and further past as far as the eye can see.
The service is outstanding.
The food of the most exceptional quality.
The experience - unforgettable.

Amazing dinning experience. The good was great, service was excellent. Amazing views of the city, beautiful decor. The chef is from Spain, he does a great job. Loved the cheese plater and deserts. Will be back.
Good experience,I went for lunch with my family. I have 3.5 years old kid but the staff took good care of everything.Very good service, fully satisfied
It goes without saying that the meals here are creative, delightful and delicious. The view of the harbour is wonderful, with the laser show being a lovely surprise.

The food was great.  I really liked the fresh pasta station. A cream sauce would have been nice but the the tomato and seafood based sauces were really tasty.  The only real negative thing was that coffee and water were not included in the high price.

reviews.text: I am happily to be here with three of my friends today to have a  lunch buffet at Hotel Ritz Carlton. The price of the lunch buffet is $598+10% service charge and luckily one of my friend got $1500 cash voucher , so we can have a unforgettable lunch at Ritz Carlton Cafe103. There were many kind of food for the lunch buffet. The seafood was very fresh and I recommend lobster and prawn it is delicious. The quality of the food was high , the customer services was good and we feel very comfortable. Even tough the lunch is expensive but we can enjoy the view of Victoria harbour , the delicious food also the services, everything is worth. At last , I would like to thanks Ritz Carlton Hong Kong for giving us a unforgettable time and memories !

I am glad to be here with my three of my friends today to try the buffet lunch at the chain hotel Ritz Carlton. The price of the buffet lunch is $598 +10% service charge and we are fortunate to get your hotel's $1500 cash voucher, so we first set foot on Ritz Carlton's Cafe103. I really can't imagine that there were so many food styles for the buffet lunch. The seafood also provided lobster and oysters, and it was also very fresh. There was no selection of low-quality ingredients for this prestigious hotel. The quality of oysters is also comparable to the taste of we had in Australia! In addition, there are many styles of hot plates, and there are all kinds of international cuisine! The number of desserts is also very refined. We have compared the sweet quality of Ritz Carlton and other hotels, and Ritz Carlton is even better! Therefore, we feel that even this lunch is expensive, but we are impressed by the food, the waiter's attentive service attitude, the constant addition of water to us, and the change of dishes. Of course, it is worth mentioning that this Victoria Harbour landscape is really unforgettable and unforgettable! At last I would like to thanks Ritz Carlton HK for giving me and my friends a very important memory of life!

Fantastic place for a special occasion located sky highat Ritz-Carlton Hotel. We went there for all you can eat seafood buffet and were not disappointed. There was a good variety of seafood, including sushi stand, but also more traditional Chinese dishes, like bbq duck, pork belly and mapo tofu. Spectacular views of Hong Kong make this experience pretty special.

My girlfriend and I enjoyed our first visit to Café 103 at The Ritz-Carlton, Hong Kong. The seating area is quite nice and serene enough for you to take in the amazing views offered from the 103rd floor overlooking Victoria Harbour. Food selection is debatable. Although quality was definitely on par, variety needs improvement for the lunch buffet. Prices are what you would expect from hotel buffets in the city center. All in all, the overall experience was good.
If you want to enjoy the best views of Hong Kong you have to visit it. Very elegant place. The desserts are by far the best in the world!

在Ritz-Carlton的103樓享用自助晚餐，看似浪漫，但可惜食物質素未達標，$832一位的價格絕對不值得👎🏻。
.

食物款式太少，吸引的更少😶。北京填鴨最「搶手」，餅皮極薄，包着鴨肉、蔥段及醬汁，吃下去一點都不油膩，實屬上品😻。其餘都不過不失，說不上難吃，但也沒有什麼值得推介。冷盤的海鮮不鮮甜，不試也罷😕。至於甜品也算得是中上，每一種都不錯，但沒有一種會令人難忘😔。
.

一頓$832的自助晚餐，大概只有四星級酒店的水準😔。餐廳名氣再大，gimmick再多，食物質素也應作為首位。連餐飲也可以整枱「漏單」，服務生也一直在偷偷摸摸地用手機。撇除悠長的升降機之旅，我也沒有辦法相信自己身處一家五星級飯店。
.

All in all, the overall experience was good.

reviews.text: I choose this hotel because I wanted to reside in the best hotel in Hong Kong.  Ritz Carlton matched 100% my expectations. The front desk service personnel was perfect. The Victoria Suite Room was really luxury and the Butler service was truly second to none. The hotel SPA is beautiful and the masseuse very capable. I got true value for my money. I certainly recommend this hotel to anyone who like me want the best.

Fabulous. I had the chance to have some drinks in the highest bar in the world! As all of the Ritz in the world, this one is a splendid site to rest. Pools, bars, comfort, and local/international food available. You wont miss a thing. Regarding to the customer service, it did match the expectations. Don't forget to ask for the lion's bag!

I booked the Ritz-Carlton recently for a two night stay for my wife and I, mainly because of the novelty of it being the highest hotel in the world, but the actual experience was so much more than that. From the moment we walked through the door we were treated like royalty, but in an incredibly warm and friendly way which didn't feel at all pretentious. The entire team seemed to go out of their way to make your stay something really special.

We were looked after by Marcus at the front desk who upgraded our room to a beautiful suite on the 116th floor giving incredible views over Hong Kong Island. We were surprised to see what I believe to be a 280cm wide bed, the biggest bed I've ever seen! Our room was on the same floor as the club lounge, where we spent a fair bit of time enjoying great food and drink, and amazing service.

My only regret about our stay here is that in two nights we didn't see as much of the city as we had imagined we would, simply because the hotel was so good that we wanted to enjoy it as much as possible. We'll definitely have to go back someday!

Thanks to all the team at the Ritz-Carlton who made our stay what it was!

I'm very impressive here. All staff very nice and  appreciate to help us. We got many kids in our trip and they take care them with a cute snack and the Ritz's lion bag including the art kits. Our kids very enjoy.

About the panorama view here is very superb, even I choose the deluxe suit I think it's worth to relax and have a nice date here.

Ahhh,, I almost forget to talk about the restroom. It's very Grand with the bath tub and their television. They provide the soap and the spa salt but I think it should be better if they have a bubble soap. I think their soap is not a good taste. It should be sweet smell more.
However, the shower set in the shower room is fine
.
Another comment is about the toilet ,, they have tissue paper but I didn't have a bin. I don't know why. It's outside the toilet so when we done we have to left it outside the toilet. I think some people might be left inside closet or they don't have any problem about that
.
Just a little problem ,,
The overall of the Ritz-Carlton HK is very nice to spend time and worthy
@papercrafter.th
.
โดยภาพรวมแล้วประทับใจมากกับที่นี่ค่ะ ในทริปของเรามีเด็กๆอยู่หลายคน ตอนที่เรามาเช็คอิน สตาฟได้เอาขนม เครื่องเขียนระบายสี และกระเป๋าสะพายสิงโตสุดน่ารัก พร้อมกับป้ายห้อยคอมาเพื่อให้เด็กๆใส่ ผู้ปกครองสามารถเขียนขื่อที่อยู่ เบอร์ติดต่อเอาไว้ได้ เผื่อน้องหลงทาง
.
รวมถึงในตอนเย็นมีขนมตกแต่งน่ารักเอาไว้เด็กๆในห้องอีกด้วย เมื่อเปิดประตูเข้ามาเด็กๆกรี๊ดเลยค่ะ แม้จะหวานเจี้ยบไปหน่อย แต่ก็ประทับใจมากๆ
.
อีกสิ่งหนึ่งนอกจากพาโนรามาวิวของริซคาลตันที่ขึ้นชื่อว่าเป็นวิวระดับไฮเอนด์ของฮ่องกงแล้ว ห้องน้ำก็ดีงามไม่แพ้กัน มีอ่างสปาพร้อมทีวีติดกระจก ให้จิบไวน์ นอนแช่ และดูหนังไปพร้อมกันได้ แต่ระวังเพลินจนตัวเปื่อยนะคะ เค้ามีสบู่และเกลือสปาเซอร์วิสให้ แต่ไม่มีบับเบิ้ลบาธ ใครที่ชอบแช่อ่างนุ่มๆ ละมุนๆ อาจจะต้องพกพาไปเองนะคะ สบู่ของเค้าไม่ค่อยหอมเท่าไหร่ด้วย พกกลิ่นที่ตัวเองชอบไปน่าจะสบายใจกว่า
.
แต่ที่ข้องใจคือ ห้องน้ำอันแยกเป็นสัดเป็นส่วนดีมาก ในห้องส้วมมีทิชชู่ แต่ไม่มีถังขยะ ทำให้ต้องเปิดประตูออกมาทิ้งข้างนอก หรือว่าโรงแรมให้ทิ้งในส้วมเลยได้นะ มันดูลำบากไปหน่อย น่าจะมีถังเอาไว้ให้
.
ห้องเราเป็นห้องดีลักซ์ และจองเตียงเสริมเอาไว้ด้วย ค่อนข้างดีทีเดียว แม้จะไม่ละมุนเหมือนเตียงใหญ่ แต่ก็เพิ่มแค่คืนละ 800HKD เท่านั้น
.
โดยรวมแล้ว คุ้มค่า ราคาไม่แพงสำหรับวิวและภาพรวมทั้งหมด การบริการสุดแสนประทับใจจริงๆ
อยากมีภาพรีวิวมากกว่านี้นะคะ แต่พอดีเด็กๆกระโดดขึ้นเตียงกันไปซะก่อน เจ่เจ้อดถ่ายเลย ^^

The hotel is a real 5 star with all attention to detail. There are a lot of art pieces everywhere. Staff are at Ritz Carlton standard. View from the room is magnificent. It is also very convenient if you take an airport express to/from the airport. The station is connected to the hotel via Elements mall. There are also Michelin star restaurants here. Fitness has great and modern equipment.
